fielddes: Unique ID of the Organization. An Organization is the concept of a company, which is constructed as a collection of Legal Entities (child and parent entities) and Locations (e.g., offices, stores).
Primary, most common name of the Organization, which equals the name of the ultimate parent or sole entity that comprises the Organization
Business name of the Organization, sometimes a DBA
DBA of the Organization, not always reported

Classification system for the Organization based on whether it is an Employer, Non-Employer, Sole Proprietor, or a Holding Company. An Employer has full-time W-2 employees in the U.S. A Non-Employer is an operating business without full-time employees. A Sole Proprietor is a micro business without full-time employees that often operates from a residential address. A Holding Company is not engaged in economic activity, and is often used for real estate and financial transactions

Multi-entity U.S. organization (a collection of legal entities with an ultimate parent in the U.S.); Multi-entity non-U.S. organization (a collection of legal entities with an ultimate parent outside the U.S.); or Single-entity organization (consists of a sole entity)

Clasification of the Legal form of the Organization of the Ultimate parent or Sole entity that comprises the Organizaation based on whether it is a Corporation, Limited Liability Company, Partnership, Non-Profit Corporation or Non-Profit Organization.
Unique number issued by the IRS given to the Organization which is used to identify the business and certain other related entities. An organization may have multiple EINs; this is the primary EIN.
The Central Index Key (CIK) is a unique number issued by the SEC.
